# Silent Doctor — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A complete local-first AI medical assistant with **20 files** across 7 packages:

```
silent_doctor/
├── main.py                          ← Interactive CLI entry point
├── requirements.txt                 ← All dependencies
├── config/settings.py               ← Centralized configuration
├── utils/helpers.py                 ← Image, audio, logging utilities
├── orchestrator/router.py           ← LangChain routing (5 pipelines)
├── models/
│   ├── skin_model.py                ← MobileNetV2 (5 skin classes)
│   └── eye_model.py                 ← MobileNetV3-Small (4 eye classes)
├── voice/
│   ├── speech_to_text.py            ← faster-whisper (INT8 quantized)
│   ├── translation.py               ← NLLB-200 via CTranslate2
│   └── tts.py                       ← Coqui XTTS v2
├── rag/
│   ├── embeddings.py                ← all-MiniLM-L6-v2
│   ├── vector_store.py              ← FAISS + PDF/text ingestion
│   └── medical_rag.py               ← RAG → Ollama (Gemma 2B)
├── modules/
│   └── child_support.py             ← Pediatric health assessment
└── datasets/                        ← Medical PDFs go here
```

## Key Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **Lazy model loading** | All models load on first use, not at startup — critical for low-RAM devices |
| **Singleton caching** | `get_*()` factory functions ensure each model loads only once |
| **LangChain `RunnableLambda`** | Clean composable routing without heavy framework overhead |
| **INT8 quantization** | Whisper + NLLB quantized for ~50% memory savings |
| **Env-var overrides** | Every model/endpoint is configurable via environment variables |
| **Medical safety prompts** | LLM always disclaims it's not a real doctor and recommends professional care |

## Voice Pipeline Flow

```
User speaks (Darija/Amazigh)
  → faster-whisper STT (auto language detection)
  → NLLB translate to English
  → RAG retrieval (FAISS) + Ollama LLM (Gemma 2B)
  → NLLB translate back to user's language
  → Coqui XTTS v2 text-to-speech
```

